wiki.summary: "Jealous" is a song by Filipino musician Eyedress, released on 6 December 2019 as a single from his album, Let's Skip to the Wedding. It first charted at number twenty four on the Billboard Hot Rock & Alternative Songs and number twenty three on the Billboard Hot Alternative Songs charts on the week of 20 February 2021, climbing to number fifteen on both charts the following week, and remaining in the Hot Rock & Alternative Songs chart for 20 weeks. wiki.content: "Jealous" is a song by Filipino musician Eyedress, released on 6 December 2019 as a single from his album, Let's Skip to the Wedding. It first charted at number twenty four on the Billboard Hot Rock & Alternative Songs and number twenty three on the Billboard Hot Alternative Songs charts on the week of 20 February 2021, climbing to number fifteen on both charts the following week, and remaining in the Hot Rock & Alternative Songs chart for 20 weeks. on 21 March 2024 received multi-platinum certification from the RIAA for selling 3,000,000 equivalent units in the United States. The song was written by Eyedress after he relocated to America from the Philippines. He recorded the song in his bedroom in Silver Lake, Los Angeles with a Teisco guitar. The music video for "Jealous", was directed by BRVINFREEZE and features Eyedress skateboarding with Kane The Menace in the Venice Beach. On March 11, 2020, an animated video for the King Krule Remix directed by Eyedress was released. Alternative Press described the video as "surreal" with "a retro video game vibe" where the musicians "set off on a â€™90s Nintendo-style skateboard race through a bizarre Minecraft universe."
